blocks.text:
To make your HTML form page look smoother and more modern, I recommend the following upgrades:

- Add some gentle transitions on input fields and the button for a “responsive” feel.
- Use subtle shadow and border effects for depth.
- Add focus effects on input fields for better accessibility.
- Smooth color blending and hover effects.
- Slightly round the corners more, with softer padding/margins.
- Use a more unified and appealing color palette.

Here’s an upgraded version of your HTML and CSS, with all changes inside the `<style>` section only (easy to revert or tweak further):

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>FreshMart Order Form</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
            background: linear-gradient(120deg, #e8f5e9 0%, #fafafa 100%);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .form-section {
            background: white;
            max-width: 410px;
            margin: 3.5em auto 0;
            padding: 2.5em 2em 2em 2em;
            border-radius: 18px;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 26px rgba(135, 187, 143, 0.09), 0 1.5px 8px rgba(70, 178, 104, 0.08);
            text-align: center;
            transition: box-shadow 0.28s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1);
        }
        .form-section:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(70, 178, 104, 0.13), 0 1.5px 10px rgba(70, 178, 104, 0.12);
        }
        input, textarea {
            width: 100%;
            margin: 1em 0;
            padding: 0.85em;
            border-radius: 9px;
            border: 1px solid #c6e0cc;
            font-size: 1.07em;
            background: #f2faf3;
            box-shadow: 0 1.5px 4px rgba(114, 195, 130, 0.08);
            transition: border-color 0.16s, box-shadow 0.25s;
        }
        input:focus, textarea:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: #49c771;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(70, 193, 117, 0.13);
            background: #f9fff8;
        }
        .button {
            background: linear-gradient(90deg,#4caf50 60%, #6ed37f 100%);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 1em 2.4em;
            border-radius: 6px;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin-top: 1em;
            font-size: 1.08em;
            font-weight: 600;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(94, 208, 129, 0.12);
            transition: background 0.17s, box-shadow 0.22s, transform 0.14s;
        }
        .button:hover, .button:focus {
            background: linear-gradient(90deg,#43b049 50%, #58ca99 100%);
            box-shadow: 0 7px 16px rgba(70, 193, 117, 0.17);
            transform: translateY(-1px) scale(1.04);
        }
        h2 {
            color: #269146;
            font-size: 2em;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin-bottom: 0.8em;
            letter-spacing: 0.03em;
        }
        p {
            color: #5f7961;
            font-size:1em;
            margin-top:1.5em
        }
        a {
            color: #359e5e;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-bottom: 1px dashed #90dfb2;
            transition: color 0.14s;
        }
        a:hover {
            color: #1d6c37;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #73b38b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="form-section">
        <h2>Quick Order / Contact Form</h2>
        <form>
            <input type="text" placeholder="Your Name" required>
            <input type="email" placeholder="Your Email" required>
            <textarea placeholder="What would you like to order or ask?" rows="5" required></textarea>
            <button type="submit" class="button">Send</button>
        </form>
        <p>
            This is a simple demo form. No data will be sent.<br>
            <a href="helo.html">&larr; Back to Home</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

